            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine omnipotentis Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> divina ordinante clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Quia regiae dignitati maxime convenit
                        aures clementiae suae fidelium precibus inclinare, idcirco omnium fidelium
                        sanctae Dei Eclesiae nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum noverit
                        industria, quoniam <rs key="#Intercessory">per interventum et petitionem
                            </rs><persName key="#Intercessory #Chancellor #Deacons">Ambrosii
                            </persName><rs key="#Deacons">diaconi</rs> et <rs key="#Chancellor"
                            >cancellarii</rs> nostri quidam noster <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Deacons #fidelisOf" ref="#people/227">Audo
                        </persName>videlicet <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs> sanctae Veronenis <rs
                            key="#Churches">eclesiae</rs> nostram regiam humiliter adiit clementiam,
                        quatenus pro amore Dei animeque nostrae remedio <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >terrolam</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >prato</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#places/306">valle Provinianense</placeName>, peninentem de eadem
                            <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Other_administrative_unit"
                                ><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Other_administrative_unit"
                                ref="#estates/172">sculdasia</geogName></rs> non longe ab <orgName
                            key="#Plebs #Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/121"><placeName
                                key="#Plebs #Churches" ref="#places/363"><rs key="#Plebs #Churches"
                                    >eclesia</rs> Beati Floriani</placeName></orgName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Slave">servo </rs>uno
                        nomine <persName key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Slave"
                            >Ursiverto</persName>, nec non in <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/59"><rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs> Verona </placeName>in
                            <rs>castro </rs>subtus Arena <rs key="#Houses">duo evoluta
                            aedificia</rs>, quae vulgo artovala dicuntur, per hoc nostrae
                        auctoritatis preceptum concedere ei in ius et proprietatem ex integro
                        dignaremur. Nos igitur ratam et iustam cius petitionem considerantes, iam
                        dictam terrolam cum prato infra has scilicet coherentias atque terminos
                        posita; ab oriente siquidem et aquilone <rs
                            key="#Confinia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Roads">via
                            publica</rs>, ab occidente <orgName key="#Plebs #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/121"><rs key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions">res
                                </rs><rs key="#Plebs #Churches">Sancti Floriani</rs></orgName>, et a
                        meridie <rs
                            key="#Confinia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Rural_communities #Common_land"
                            >plures homines habentes</rs>, hec non et prenominatum servum iuris
                        regni nostri, seu et prelibata aedificia duo in castro iam dicto non longe a
                            <rs key="#Houses">mansione</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests">Georgii <rs key="#Priests">presbiteri
                            </rs></persName>per hoc nostrae regiae auctoritatis preceptum iure
                        proprietario concedimus, et de nostro iure et dominio in eius ius et
                        dominium. modis omnibus transfundimus et perdonamus nostra regia pienissima
                        largietate, ut habeat, teneat, possideat faciatque ex omnibus iam dictus
                        Audo diaconus quicquid eius decreverit animus vel voluntas, potestatemque
                        habeat donandi, vendendi, commutandi, pro anima iudicandi seu quicquid
                        voluerit in omnibus faciendi, absque alicuius potestas contradictione vel
                        minoratione. Contra quod nostrae donationis [preceptum si quis insurgere
                        temptaverit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras
                            centum</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere palatii</rs>
                        nostri et medietatem iam dicto Audoni diacono aut cui ipse dederit. Quod ut
                        verius ab omnibus credatur, manu propria firma[vimus et anul]i nostri
                        impressione subter iussimus insigniri. Signum domni (MF) Berengarii
                        serenissimi regis. <persName key="#Chancellor">Ambrosius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi </persName><rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii </rs>recognovi et subscripsi. (SR) (SI n.II) Data kal.
                        aug., anno domi(ni)cae incarnationis .DCCCCV., regni vero domni Berengarii
                        piissimi re[gis .XVIII.] indictione .VIII. Actum
                            <placeName>Tulles</placeName>. in Dei nomine feliciter, amen. </ab>
                </div>
